  schema:name "Genealogy (Lesson)" ;
  schema:description "How Foucault (after Nietzsche) traces the contingent, conflict-ridden history that produces what presents itself as natural — through descent (heterogeneous origins) and emergence (the confrontation that assembles them)." ;
